OL,3,CCalls to enforce heavy vehicle speed
OL,4,Climit law
OL,6,FHundreds of drivers in Guernsey could
OL,7,Fbe unknowingly breaking the law due to
OL,8,Fthe weight of their vehicles.
OL,10,FUnder the Road Traffic 1987 law, any
OL,11,Fnon-commercial automobile that weighs
OL,12,Fover two tonnes and exceeds 25mph is
OL,13,Fbreaking the law.
OL,15,FHowever, there are concerns from the
OL,16,FCommittee for Home Affairs that this
OL,17,Flaw is not being enforced enough.
