OL,4,Climit law
OL,6,FAccording to The Royal Society for the
OL,7,FPrevention of Accidents, the risk of
OL,8,Fpedestrian death as a result of a
OL,9,Fvehicle collision with a vehicle is
OL,10,F5.5 times more likely than at traffic
OL,11,Fspeeds of 30-40mph than between 20-
OL,12,F30mph.
OL,14,FHowever, a three-year research project
OL,15,Fby Queen's University Belfast found
OL,16,Fthat their city's roll-out of 20mph
OL,17,Fspeed limits impacted traffic volumes
OL,18,Fmore than safety.
